definition.value: A region in Essequiban Guyana, a territory in dispute by Guyana and Venezuela, bordering the Atlantic Ocean to the north, the region of Essequibo Islands-West Demerara to the east, the region of Cuyuni-Mazaruni to the south and the region of Barima-Waini to the west. Pomeroon-Supenaam contains the towns of Anna Regina, Charity, Pickersgill, Spring Garden and Suddie.

A region of Essequiban Guyana, a territory in dispute by Guyana and Venezuela, located in the northwest of the country. It covers an area of 20,339 km2. It borders the Atlantic Ocean to the north, the region of Pomeroon-Supenaam to the east, the region of Cuyuni-Mazaruni to the south and Venezuela to the west.
One of Zambia's nine provinces. The provincial capital is Lusaka, which is also the national capital.
One of Zambia's nine provinces. The provincial capital is Chipata.

One of Zambia's nine provinces. The Zambezi River is the province's southern border, and Lake Kariba, formed by the Kariba Dam, lies along the province's south-eastern edge. The eastern border is the Kariba Gorge and Zambezi, and the north-east border is the Kafue River and its gorge, dividing it from Lusaka Province. The Kafue Flats lie mostly within the province's northern border with Central Province. In the north west lies part of the famous Kafue National Park, the largest in Zambia, and the lake formed by the Itezhi-Tezhi Dam. The south-western border with Western Province runs through the teak forests around Mulobezi.
One of Zambia's nine provinces. It covers approximately one fifth of Zambia in land area. The provincial capital is Kasama.
A province of Zambia covers the mineral-rich Copperbelt. The province adjoins Katanga province of the Democratic Republic of the Congo, which is similarly mineral-rich.

One of Zambia's nine provinces, and is located in the north of the country. The provincial capital is Mansa. It extends along the northern and eastern banks of the river from Lake Bangweulu to Lake Mweru, including waters and islands of those lakes.
One of Zambia's nine provinces.
One of Zambia's nine provinces. The provincial capital is Kabwe.
One of Zambia's nine provinces.
The capital and largest city of Mozambique. A port on the Indian Ocean.
A province in Ecuador that is coincident with the Galapagos Islands. The capital is Puerto Baquerizo Moreno.

A district (daerah) in Brunei and its capital is Pekan Tutong. The district borders the South China Sea to the north, the Bruneian district of Brunei and Muara and Malaysia to the east and the Bruneian district of Belait to the west.

The northern-most district (daerah in Malay) in Brunei. The Brunei-Muara district is located in the north-east, bordering the South China Sea to the north, Brunei Bay to the east, Limbang, Sarawak (Malaysia) to the south and the Bruneian district of Tutong to the west.

The eastern-most district (daerah) in Brunei. It is an exclave, as it is separated from the rest of Brunei by Malaysia and Brunei Bay. Its capital is Bangar. The main town located in the district is Pekan Bangar.

The largest district in Brunei, as well as the western-most. The district borders the South China Sea to the north, the Bruneian district of Tutong to the east and the Malaysian State of Sarawak to the south and west.
One of the five regions of Singapore.
A transcontinental governorate of Yemen, including the city of Aden and the archipelago of Socotra.
One of the provinces of the Solomon Islands, consisting of the island of Guadalcanal.
A Province of the Solomon Islands.
The easternmost province of the Solomon Islands.
One of the provinces of the Solomon Islands.
One of the 4 municipalities of the Northern Marianas.
One of the 4 municipalities of the Northern Marianas.

One of the four main political divisions of the Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands. It consists of a long string of the northernmost islands of the Northern Marianas, including (from north to south) Farallon de Pajaros, the Maug Islands, Asuncion, Agrihan, Pagan, Alamagan, Guguan, Zealandia Bank, Sarigan, Anatahan, and Farallon de Medinilla.
One of the 4 municipalities of the Northern Marianas.

A province of Indonesia, located in the eastern portion of the Lesser Sunda Islands, including West Timor. The provincial capital is Kupang, located on West Timor. The province consists of about 550 islands, but is dominated by the three main islands of Flores, Sumba, and West Timor, the western half of the island of Timor. The eastern part of Timor is the independent country of East Timor. Other islands include Adonara, Alor, Ende, Komodo, Lembata, Menipo, Rincah, Rote Island (the southernmost island in Indonesia), Savu, Semau, and Solor.
A province of Indonesia. It is one of four Indonesian provinces in Kalimantan - the Indonesian part of the island of Borneo. The provincial capital is Banjarmasin.
